15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 14-105, as
17 amended by Section 1, Chapter 292, O.S.L. 2022 (26 O.S. Supp. 2024,
18 Section 14-105), is amended to read as follows:
19 Section 14-105. A. Any registered voter may apply for an
20 absentee ballot in person at the county election board, by United
21 States mail, by facsimile device as defined in Section 1862 of Title
22 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes or by a means of electronic
23 communication designated by the Secretary of the State Election
24 Board. The Secretary of the State Election Board shall prescribe a
