22 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 14-103.1 of Title 26, unless
24 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
Req. No. 12732 Page 4

1 A registered voter who requests an absentee ballot pursuant to
2 the provisions of Title 26 of the Oklahoma Statutes, unless
3 otherwise permitted by federal or state law, shall indicate on the
4 application the election date for which the absentee ballots are
5 requested. The application shall only be valid for the elections
6 held on that election date in which the voter is eligible to vote.
7 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
